From: Jim Huang <jserv@ccns.ncku.edu.tw>
Subject: [PATCH] arm: add GCC Link Time Optimization (LTO) support

Add CONFIG_LTO_GCC to enable GCC link-time optimization for ARM.
The implementation routes the final link through a gcc-ld wrapper so
GCC can perform whole-program optimization across translation units,
then emit native code in a single LTO pass.

Measured on MPS2-AN386 (Cortex-M4, Thumb-2, nommu) with GCC 15.2.0
and Linux 7.0, comparing mps2_defconfig builds with and without LTO:

  Section      Baseline       LTO      Delta
  .text       2,087,552  1,993,384   -94,168  (-4.5%)
  .rodata       684,000    304,464  -379,536  (-55.5%)
  .data         296,032    295,808      -224  (-0.1%)
  .bss          106,940    106,872       -68  (~0%)
  Image (raw) 3,351,648  2,868,096  -483,552  (-14.4%)

The text reduction comes from cross-TU dead code elimination and
inlining.  The large rodata drop is from unreferenced string and
table elimination that per-TU compilation cannot detect.

Six ARM/Thumb-2-specific issues required workarounds:

1. Top-level Kbuild: the original patch used KBUILD_CFLAGS to
   disable LTO for bounds.s generation, but KBUILD_CFLAGS is
   exported and the -fno-lto leaked into every sub-make, silently
   canceling LTO project-wide.  Use per-target CFLAGS_bounds.s
   and CFLAGS_devicetable-offsets.s instead.

2. Arch flags in LTO link: GCC LTO defaults to armv4t when the
   architecture is not explicitly passed to the link step.
   ARMv4T only supports Thumb-1 (immediates 0-255), so the
   assembler rejects valid Thumb-2 constants with "invalid
   constant after fixup".  Propagate $(CFLAGS_ABI), $(CFLAGS_ISA),
   and $(arch-y) through lto-flags-y.

3. Boot decompressor: arch/arm/boot/compressed/ is a standalone
   stub that runs before the kernel.  It must be compiled without
   LTO because it is linked with plain ld, which cannot process
   LTO bitcode objects.

4. Function-name ambiguity: GCC LTO disambiguates static symbols
   by appending "file.c.HASH" to their names.  When the source
   file is kernel/exit.c, the resulting symbol "exit.c.9df4f30e"
   starts with "exit." -- a prefix that scripts/check-function-
   names.sh rejects to prevent section-name collisions with
   -ffunction-sections.  The check is a kernel-side script, not a
   GCC diagnostic.  Suppress it under CONFIG_LTO_GCC and add
   -fno-function-sections to KBUILD_CFLAGS so GCC does not record
   function-section metadata in the LTO bytecode.

5. Branch range overflow: LTO merges all .text into a single
   section, which can push call targets beyond the +-1 MB range
   of Thumb-2 conditional branches (B<cond>.W / R_ARM_THM_JUMP19).
   In entry-common.S, "bcs arm_syscall" overflows after LTO code
   merging.  Restructure as "bcc 1f; b arm_syscall; 1:" -- the
   short conditional forward branch stays in range while the
   unconditional B.W has +-16 MB reach.  Also pass
   -fno-reorder-functions to limit layout churn.

6. Kallsyms instability: LTO-mangled symbol names (.lto_priv.N,
   file.c.HASH suffixes) change the kallsyms data size between
   passes, preventing convergence even with KALLSYMS_EXTRA_PASS.
   Disable CONFIG_KALLSYMS in build.sh (also saves space on this
   memory-constrained target).

Additional infrastructure ported from the linux-lto project:

- scripts/Makefile.lto: -flto, DISABLE_LTO_GCC, gcc-ar/gcc-nm,
  LDFINAL via gcc-ld wrapper, TMPDIR override
- scripts/gcc-ld: translates ld command-line to gcc invocation
- LDFINAL plumbing in Makefile.vmlinux_o, Makefile.vmlinux,
  Makefile.build, Makefile.modfinal, link-vmlinux.sh
- __noreorder on initcalls to stabilize .initcall section order
- __visible on irq_enter_rcu, irq_exit_rcu,
  raw_irqentry_exit_cond_resched, __static_call_return0
  (assembly-referenced, LTO would otherwise internalize them)
- __flatten disabled under LTO (triggers GCC ICE with
  whole-program)
- __visible_on_lto / __global_on_lto helpers
- DISABLE_LTO_GCC on files that break under LTO: cache.o,
  string.o, version-timestamp.o, .vmlinux.export.o
- KASAN: BUILD_BUG() -> break, __used on shadow mem*
- bloat-o-meter / mksysmap awareness of .lto_priv symbols
- Livepatch depends on !LTO_GCC
- CONFIG_LTO guard changed to CONFIG_LTO_CLANG where appropriate
- delay-objtool keyed on CONFIG_LTO (covers both Clang and GCC)
- cond_syscall / SYSCALL_ALIAS compat_## aliases for LTO linking

